(c) Train a mask condition controller jointly on the mask-annotated source-domain dataset洧릅subscript洧洧\mathcal{D}_{s}caligraphic_D start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_s end_POSTSUBSCRIPTand unannotated target-domain dataset洧릆subscript洧洧노\mathcal{D}_{t}caligraphic_D start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_t end_POSTSUBSCRIPT, enabling controllable generation based on both text prompts and masks.

Figure 8:Failure Cases Analysis.Our proposed MRGen is not without limitations:
(a) it may struggle to handle extremely small organ masks;
(b) it occasionally produces false-negative samples, such as the unexpected synthesis of kidneys in the given example.
